cc:Work.dc:description: # AD8232 ECG preamplifier `The AD8233 Heart Rate Monitor Front End is an integrated signal conditioning block for ECG and other biopotential measurement applications. It is designed to extract, amplify, and filter small biopotential signals in the presence of noisy conditions` The output from this sensitive amplifier can be monitored by the analog inputs of SEELab3/ExpEYES17. ## Connections Only 3 connections need be made + 3.3V ( CS1, CS2, CS3, CS4 ) . Or use a 3.3V regulator via 5V + GND + Output of the module to A1 ## Sample Data from the author I connected electrodes across my chest and the reference electrode at the bottom right of my stomach and obtained the following plot Much cleaner data can be obtained. ## More fun stuff The electrodes can be connected at various parts of the body to record various neurological signals from muscles, eyes etc.
